## **STEP 1 — Modularize the Admin Tools (safe, no engine changes)**  
Break NodeEditor.js into:
- NodeEditor.core.js  
- NodeEditor.visual.js  
- NodeEditor.effects.js  
- NodeEditor.advanced.js  
- NodeEditor.types.js  

Break AdminDashboard.js into:
- dashboard.core.js  
- dashboard.hunts.js  
- dashboard.panels.js  
- dashboard.modals.js  

**Why:**  
Cleaner, safer, easier to maintain, easier to add new node types.

---

## **STEP 2 — Modularize game.js (the right way)**  
Split into:
- game.runtime.js  
- game.renderer.js  
- game.transitions.js  
- game.inventory.js  
- game.effects.js  
- game.nodeTypes.js  

**Why:**  
Multiplayer, templates, and new node types will require a clean engine.

